Research
Interests
I wish to understand the foundations of learning and decision making towards developing intelligent
systems. My approach forges connections between different disciplines, and is often focused on dis-
covering scientifically interpretable structure in data. I am particularly engaged in building methods
for probabilistic deep learning, scalable Gaussian processes, physics-inspired machine learning, AI
alignment, kernel learning, and training of deep neural networks. I have applied my work to time
series, vision, spatial statistics, NLP, counterfactual inference, public policy, medicine, and physics.
I also believe in reproducible research, and my work is the basis for several open-source libraries.
